Some exome assay specific BED files to be used as TARGETFILE for tCoNuT can be downloaded from ... .  These files
where generated from targets files that are associated with exome kits.  An overlap
with targets and exon BED files is done to ensure regions between targets are included.
In addition each exon is padded with 150 bases on each side.

If you don't find your kit TARGETSFILE at ... , you can generate one using the createBED.sh script. 

However you generate your TARGETSFILE it has to contain 30956976 lines with these starting and ending lines:

1	0	100	0
...
25	16600	16700 0

Format is CHR START END FLAG. FLAG is 0 == region to remove, 0 > region to keep.
